## Test Tagging Convention

Use tags to categorize tests for selective execution:

```typescript
test.describe('Feature Tests @feature @regression', () => {
  test('should do something @smoke @prod', async () => {});
  test('should do something else @local', async () => {});
});
```

### Standard Tags
- `@smoke` - Quick smoke tests, run on every deployment
- `@regression` - Full regression tests
- `@prod` - Safe to run in production (read-only)
- `@local` - Only for local development (may modify data)
- `@critical` - Critical path tests
- `@e2e` - Full end-to-end tests
- `@api` - API-level tests

### Feature Tags
- `@finances` - Financial module tests
- `@rent-payments` - Rent payments page
- `@security-deposits` - Security deposits page
- `@invoices` - Invoices page
- `@late-fees` - Late fees page
- `@net-worth` - Net worth tracking
- `@investments` - Investment analysis

### Quality Tags
- `@performance` - Performance tests
- `@responsive` - Responsive design tests
- `@error` - Error handling tests

