## Page Object Model Pattern

### Base Page Class
All page objects extend `BasePage` which provides common functionality:

```typescript
import { Page, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import { BasePage } from './base-page';
import TestConfig from '../config/test-config';

export class MyFeaturePage extends BasePage {
  // Private selectors using data-testid when available
  private readonly pageContainer = '[data-testid="feature-page"]';
  private readonly submitButton = '[data-testid="submit-btn"]';
  
  constructor(page: Page) {
    super(page);
  }

  async goto(): Promise<void> {
    await this.page.goto('/feature-path');
    await this.waitForPageLoad();
  }

  async verifyPageDisplayed(): Promise<void> {
    await expect(this.page.locator(this.pageContainer))
      .toBeVisible({ timeout: TestConfig.timeouts.medium });
  }
  
  // Always wait for data to load
  async waitForDataLoad(): Promise<void> {
    await this.waitForLoadingComplete();
    await Promise.race([
      this.page.locator('.data-table').waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15000 }),
      this.page.locator('.empty-state').waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15000 })
    ]).catch(() => {});
  }
}
```

### Selector Best Practices
1. **Prefer `data-testid` attributes** - Most reliable
2. **Use semantic selectors** - `role`, `label`, `text` when data-testid unavailable
3. **Avoid brittle selectors** - No `.class-name:nth-child(2)` patterns
4. **Handle PrimeNG components** - Many have nested inputs

```typescript
// Good selectors
private readonly emailInput = '[data-testid="email-input"]';
private readonly submitButton = 'p-button[data-testid="submit"]';
private readonly pageTitle = 'h1:has-text("My Page")';

// For PrimeNG components with nested inputs
const input = this.page.locator('[data-testid="amount-input"]').locator('input');
await input.fill('100');
```

