## Common Patterns

### Handling Rate Limiting
The Auth API has rate limiting. Handle gracefully:
```typescript
// In fixtures, rate limiting is handled with exponential backoff
// In tests, skip if authentication fails
test.beforeEach(async ({ demoUsersAvailable }) => {
  test.skip(!demoUsersAvailable, 'Demo users not seeded');
});
```

### Waiting for Dynamic Content
```typescript
// Wait for either success or empty state
await Promise.race([
  this.page.locator('.data-table').waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15000 }),
  this.page.locator('.empty-state').waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 15000 })
]).catch(() => {});

// Wait for loading to complete
async waitForLoadingComplete(): Promise<void> {
  const loadingIndicator = this.page.locator('p-progressSpinner, .loading');
  await loadingIndicator.waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 30000 }).catch(() => {});
}
```

### Handling PrimeNG Components
```typescript
// Dropdown/Select
await this.page.locator('p-select').click();
await this.page.locator('li:has-text("Option")').click();

// Dialog
const dialog = this.page.locator('p-dialog');
await expect(dialog).toBeVisible();
await dialog.locator('p-button:has-text("Save")').click();

// Table
const rows = this.page.locator('p-table tbody tr');
const count = await rows.count();
```

### Test Data Management
```typescript
// Create data for test
const user = await testDataManager.createTestUser();

// Data is automatically cleaned up after test via fixture
```

